---
/**
 * watermarks-deep-dive · Figure 4 — Level 4: three independent questions
 * (where / when / how), the watermark only informs the middle one.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/streaming-event-driven/watermarks-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component for the same reason as
 * Fig1: raw inline SVG with kebab-case attributes is unreliable inside MDX. This
 * figure references no arrowhead markers, so it needs no local <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Three independent questions: where in event time (windowing), when in processing time (triggers), and how successive results relate (accumulation). The watermark only informs the when."
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect x="14" y="30" width="178" height="86" rx="10" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text
                x="103"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">WHERE</text
            >
            <text x="103" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >in event time?</text
            >
            <text x="103" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#111110"
                >→ windowing</text
            >
            <rect
                x="211"
                y="30"
                width="178"
                height="86"
                rx="10"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">WHEN</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >in processing time?</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#111110"
                >→ triggers</text
            >
            <rect x="408" y="30" width="178" height="86" rx="10" fill="#fff" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="497"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">HOW</text
            >
            <text x="497" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >do results relate?</text
            >
            <text x="497" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#111110"
                >→ accumulation</text
            >
            <text
                x="300"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110"
                >THREE INDEPENDENT QUESTIONS — the watermark only INFORMS the middle one</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="136" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >the watermark does NOT decide when a window fires</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Where → windowing · When → triggers · How → accumulation. The watermark <em>informs</em> the on-time
        firing; it does not answer "when".
    </figcaption>
</figure>
